### dotnet-orders demo
### Open in VS Code (REST Client extension), Visual Studio, or Rider's HTTP client
### and run each request with the "Send Request" / play button.

@host = http://localhost:8082
# When recording with proxymock (`make record`), point at the recorder instead:
# @host = http://localhost:4143

### 1 - Create an order. The response returns a freshly generated "orderId".
POST {{host}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "item": "widget",
  "quantity": 2
}

### 2 - Confirm the order.
### Copy the "orderId" from the response above and paste it below by hand.
### Yes - this manual copy-paste is the annoying part. It is exactly what
### proxymock's Smart Replace ("Correlated ID") recommendation automates so your
### recorded traffic replays with the right id every time, no hand-editing.
POST {{host}}/orders/confirm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "paste-orderId-from-step-1-here"
}

### 3 - List all orders
GET {{host}}/orders
